top.value: Oxfam investment in partnership with countries to strengthen DRR strategies by building absorptive, adaptive, and transformative capacities of local communities to assert their rights in complex and multi-hazard environments.

Evaluations to improve the effectiveness of Oxfam interventions and expand our knowledge on key issues related to OUS thematic programming. They are also proposed and led by country offices, on a program they regard as important to their portfolio.

The Africa innovative grants were aimed to support OI countries to work towards new ways of working or demonstrate a repeatable new approach that could be applied more widely as well as contribute to leverage influencing opportunities

Project supports the management and new program development within human rights and fiscal justice work, promotes learning from past experience, and encourages research leading to program and advocacy work in the US and abroad.
This project focuses on advocacy to increase public investment, including foreign assistance, in agriculture and improved agriculture policies within African nations.

Saving for Change is an innovative savings groups program that builds resilience and promotes women's empowerment. Since 2005, Oxfam and key collaborators, provide basic financial services to women around the world.
